description:
&lt;p&gt;We have an outstanding opportunity for a highly motivated Senior Respiratory Physiologist to join our amazing team in the Respiratory and Sleep Physiology Department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be joining a thriving and extremely supportive team which comprises of 10 Respiratory&lt;em&gt; C&lt;/em&gt;onsultants across the two hospital sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are entering an exciting phase of developing the Respiratory Department, with new services for our airways team, supporting innovation and research in to vocal cord dysfunction, breathing pattern disorders and complex asthma. We also continue to improve and expand our Sleep and CPAP services, and hope to provide support of our expanding NIV service. Currently the Department is at the point of expansion and is being re-sited into a larger fit for purpose space.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be responsible for the delivery of a wide range of respiratory investigations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate must be able to perform a full range of investigations including Spirometry, Diffusion studies, Plethysmography, Bronchial challenge testing, Six minute walks, Muscle pressure tests ( MIPS/MEPS/SNIP), Respiratory sleep studies, overnight pulse oximetry. Experience in CPET, CPAP and Sleep Services would also be desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Continuous professional development is strongly encouraged and you will have excellent opportunities to develop further your skills and knowledge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview Date: 18th December 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
